[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Adds proper support for modern displays — your monitor's native resolution, higher refresh rates, zoom, HUD scaling, and fog control.[/size]

[size=3][b]Resolution and refresh[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Native resolution[/b] — your main display's native resolution is added to the in-game resolution dropdown (vanilla's list is capped below modern monitors).[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Refresh-rate cap matched to your monitor[/b] — vanilla's VSYNC caps the game at 60 FPS regardless of display. This mod raises the cap to whatever your monitor reports (144, 165, 240, etc.) so the game runs smoothly at your actual refresh rate.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu artwork[/b] rescales to fit the chosen resolution so it's no longer stretched or letterboxed.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Camera and HUD[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Zoom in/out[/b] — default + and − keys (rebindable), or use the in-game F1 config slider. No unlock required — zoom works anywhere.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]HUD scale[/b] — resize the main HUD from tiny to oversized to suit your monitor.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]HUD X/Y position[/b] — independent X and Y offsets so the HUD can be nudged to the spot that fits your layout.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Environment[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Wind effect rescaling[/b] — scales the vanilla wind overlay correctly for non-standard resolutions.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Disable fog option[/b] — if fog still renders oddly at your resolution, turn it off in the F1 config. (Fog is a more complex overlay than the rest, which is why it has its own toggle.)[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Troubleshooting — 4K / high-DPI resolution[/b][/size]

[size=3][b]The mod now applies this fix for you automatically.[/b] On first launch with Windows display scaling set above 100%, Show Me Moar detects it and offers to apply the fix via a main-menu dialog. Click Yes, restart the game, done. You can apply, undo, or silence the prompt any time under the "── 9. High-DPI Fix ──" settings section (press F1 in-game).[/size]

[size=3]The manual steps below still work if you prefer to do it yourself, or if the automatic fix fails for any reason (e.g. the game folder is read-only — in that case the mod applies the registry half but skips the sidecar manifest).[/size]

[list]
[*][size=3]Open the game folder ([code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper[/code])[/size]
[*][size=3]Right-click [code]Graveyard Keeper.exe[/code] and select Properties[/size]
[*][size=3]Go to the Compatibility tab[/size]
[*][size=3]Click "Change high DPI settings"[/size]
[*][size=3]Turn on "High DPI scaling override" and set it to "Application"[/size]
[*][size=3]Launch the game[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Main menu still looks blurry after the restart?[/b] This is normal on first launch. Open the in-game Settings → Display, change the resolution to anything else, then back to your native resolution. The render output snaps to the correct DPI from that point on, including the main menu next time you launch.[/size]

[size=3]If it's still wrong after that, [b]cache-kick Windows[/b] — open Settings → System → Display → Scale, change it one step up, then back down to your original value. This forces Windows to re-read the compatibility flag for an app that was already registered.[/size]

